obile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526342\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 18, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104cai1665702876465.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cai1665702876465.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cai1665702876465.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"cai1665702876465\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Ensure TCP/IP Connectivity\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Follow the procedure to ensure a valid TCP/IP connection.</p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"cai1665702876465__li_d28829e1_d28830e1_d28831e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"cai1665702876465__p_d66095e1_d66096e1_d66097e1\">Ensure that there is a TCP/IP port available for\n               use by the Uniface Router.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">In this documentation, 13001 is assumed to be the port used. To restrict the\n                  TCP/IP port for use only by Uniface, reserve TCP/IP ports for Uniface:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cai1665702876465__li_d28832e1_d28833e1_d28834e1\">Enter <code class=\"ph codeph\">GO CMDTCP</code> and select\n                        <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Add TCP/IP Port Restriction</span>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cai1665702876465__li_d28835e1_d28836e1_d28837e1\">Set the range of restricted ports and the\n                     *TCP protocol. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cai1665702876465__li_d28838e1_d28839e1_d28840e1\">Set the user profile that owns the UROUTER\n                     job as the user profile. </li>\n</ol>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cai1665702876465__p_d66098e1_d66099e1_d66100e1\">TCP/IP port assignment is optional and *IOSYSCFG\n                  authority is required to change the port assignment.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"cai1665702876465__li_d28841e1_d28842e1_d28843e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"cai1665702876465__p_d66101e1_d66102e1_d66103e1\">Ensure that TCP services are running.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">Use the <code class=\"ph codeph\">WRKTCPSTS</code> command, specifying option 1, to verify that\n               the TCP/IP interface is active.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"cai1665702876465__li_d28844e1_d28845e1_d28846e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Ensure that your TCP/IP host and domain name are correctly configured.\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"cai1665702876465__li_d28847e1_d28848e1_d28849e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Use the CL command <code class=\"ph codeph\">CHGTCPDMN</code> to ensure the fields <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Host name</span> and <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Domain name</span> are filled correctly. Otherwise the Uniface Router and/or Uniface Server may not work as expected.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"cai1665702876465__li_d28850e1_d28851e1_d28852e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Check that you have correctly specified at least one Domain name server on page 2 of <code class=\"ph codeph\">CHGTCPDMN</code>, or that you entered the host name in the local host table using <code class=\"ph codeph\">ADDTCPHTE</code>.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"cai1665702876465__li_d28853e1_d28854e1_d28855e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Verify your domain name server or host table entry by checking that you can <code class=\"ph codeph\">ping</code> the iSeries system by its host name on the system itself.\n </span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526342\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526342\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Ensure TCP/IP Connectivity Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 18, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Ensure TCP/IP Connectivity Follow the procedure to ensure a valid TCP/IP connection. Ensure that there is a TCP/IP port available for use by the Uniface Router. In this documentation, 13001 is assumed to be the port used. To restrict the TCP/IP port for use only by Uniface, reserve TCP/IP ports for Uniface: Enter GO CMDTCP and select Add TCP/IP Port Restriction . Set the range of restricted ports and the *TCP protocol. Set the user profile that owns the UROUTER job as the user profile. TCP/IP port assignment is optional and *IOSYSCFG authority is required to change the port assignment. Ensure that TCP services are running. Use the WRKTCPSTS command, specifying option 1, to verify that the TCP/IP interface is active. Ensure that your TCP/IP host and domain name are correctly configured. Use the CL command CHGTCPDMN to ensure the fields Host name and Domain name are filled correctly. Otherwise the Uniface Router and/or Uniface Server may not work as expected. Check that you have correctly specified at least one Domain name server on page 2 of CHGTCPDMN , or that you entered the host name in the local host table using ADDTCPHTE . Verify your domain name server or host table entry by checking that you can ping the iSeries system by its host name on the system itself. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}